post_text:
We are moving to Level 3 Rattler Dens! Here is the information for 6th grade. We will start Level 3 Rattler Dens next week, the week of August 31-September 4th! Your child will come to school on their assigned Rattler Den Days. Students may enter the building at 7:30am and will be dismissed at 1:30pm. Your child may be asked to attend on Friday for additional support, testing, or other academic needs. This additional day will be by appointment. Your student will complete virtual assignments online the rest of the week. Please give us a call if you have questions or if you do not see your child's name on the list. 866-900-2001
Go Rattlers!!!

post_text: For the game against Paris tomorrow night we have been allotted 100 tickets due to COVID-19 restrictions. We are asking that everyone allow parents of our football players to purchase their tickets first ($5 per person). Parents will have until noon tomorrow. Parents please only purchase the absolutely necessary number of tickets for your immediate family. Please understand that we have over 47 players, which works out to about 2 tickets per player if all things are even. After noon tomorow, that we will open up ticket sales, first come first serve. We are sorry for any inconvenience that this causes. We know we all want to cheer on our Rattlers!

post_text: We have just received word from the Deputy Commissioner, Ivy Pfeffer, that all schools will have a uniform start date. We along with all other schools in Arkansas will be starting August 24th. This will allow DESE and the Department of Health to have a more wholistic approach. Please understand this continues to be a very fluid situation and may change. In the next couple of weeks we will be working to build a new school calendar. This new calendar will be released as soon as possible. Thank you for understanding.

Thank you in advance for your understanding.

post_text:
Here is some more important information we want to pass along to all of our families who were receiving Free/Reduced Meal Benefits:

Eligible students and families will receive food benefits on a new or existing EBT card to help fill the gap left by missed access to school meals during COVID closures.

This will be paid in a one-time payment ($319 per eligible child) and will be issued to SNAP families on their existing EBT cards, and to non-SNAP families on a new EBT card by the end of June or beginning of July.

If you are eligible for these benefits, but have had a change of address since March, you must update your information BEFORE JUNE 15TH in order to receive them.

SNAP Families- Call Client Assistance at 1-800-482-8988.
Non-SNAP Families- Email updated information to pebt@dhs.arkansas.gov (or you can call the number above as well.)

Don't forget the deadline to change/update information for this is Monday June 15th!

post_text:
We know waiting has been hard, as of 4:12 this afternoon we have an ADE/ADH approved graduation plan!
Activities will be held on May 22nd. Seniors please be sure you are checking your email and sharing that information with your parents. The district will be premiering the graduation video followed by a diploma drive-through on Friday evening. (Announcement on air time will be coming soon.) This is the only district led non-traditional graduation activity that we are permitted to hold. We are planning to have a traditional graduation ceremony July 10th, if it is allowed at that time by the Governor and Department of Health. If graduations are still disallowed we will schedule it for a later date. We are committed to making sure that the Class of 2020 have their much deserved traditional graduation. Thank you all for your patience.

Thank you all for your patience.

post_text: This has been a crazy year for our seniors! Though I always think yearbooks are important, I think this year they may mean a little bit more to our seniors who missed out on other memories. Consider donating a yearbook to a senior this year. I will put seniors who did not order one in a basket and draw names for the donated books. If you want it to go to a particular student, you can put their name in instead of “senior donation.” If there are more books donated than seniors who do not have them, I will pass out to juniors and so on. If you have any questions, you can contact me at Andrea.dewitt@magazinek12.com. Thank you!

Bucket Filling is actions or words that show that you care about someone. Saying or doing something kind. Giving someone a heartfelt smile. Using names with respect. Helping without being asked. Giving sincere compliments. Showing respect to others. There are hundreds of wonderful ways to fill buckets. The language of bucket filling has become synonymous with being kind and thoughtful. Your bucket will be filled when, at the close of each day, you reflect on the ways in which you have filled buckets.

Serenity Mora and Cecilia Mora
have been making masks that will go to community helpers in Logan County

post_text:
Census 2020: Arkansas is currently falling behind the national response rate, and some areas of the state are very far behind. For each person not counted,we could lose $33,000 in federal funds over the next decade.
The 2020 Census helps decide how much money communities will get for schools, child care and early learning, health insurance and medical care, early intervention and home visiting programs, food assistance, foster care, housing assistance, and public transport. It only takes 10 minutes, but it will impact the next 10 years.
Take the Census online, or call 844-330-2020 to complete the form by phone in English or find other by phone language options here. Let’s do this together and bring more resources to Logan County!

post_text:
Bucket Filling is actions or words that show that you care about someone. Saying or doing something kind. Giving someone a heartfelt smile. Using names with respect. Helping without being asked. Giving sincere compliments. Showing respect to others. There are hundreds of wonderful ways to fill buckets. The language of bucket filling has become synonymous with being kind and thoughtful. Your bucket will be filled when, at the close of each day, you reflect on the ways in which you have filled buckets.

Raylee Bates, Eli Gleason, Zoey Thurman

shared_text:
Magazine School District
January 29 at 12:21 PM ·

This year's flu has hit hard, after conferring with administrators, coaches, and healthcare officials, we have decided to use two AMI days for this Thursday(Jan. 30th) and Friday(Jan. 31st). We have too many students, teachers and staff out sick to effectively conduct school, and this will give everyone the chance to get well.

There will be no 7th grade or Jr. high games Thursday against County Line, but Jr. Girls and both Senior Teams will travel to Mountainburg Friday night.

Parents, please wash your child's coats, jackets, backpacks, lunch boxes, etc. with a disinfectant cleaner before they return to school. Please see that their hair is washed, and emphasize the importance of handwashing.

Again, Magazine School District will not be in session tomorrow (Jan. 30th) and Friday (Jan. 31st) due to illness. We will use 2 AMI days.

There will be no 7th grade or Jr. high games Thursday against County Line, but Jr. Girls and both Senior Teams will travel to Mountainburg Friday night.

Parents, please wash your child's coats, jackets, backpacks, lunch boxes, etc. with a disinfectant cleaner before they return to school. Please see that their hair is washed, and emphasize the importance of handwashing.

Again, Magazine School District will not be in session tomorrow (Jan. 30th) and Friday (Jan. 31st) due to illness. We will use 2 AMI days.
